deck_excerpt: An Exodia deck which draws like crazy and stuns the opponent (2022)
deck_description:
Hi fellow Exodia players here's a decklist I adapted to the modern game, but based on the deck I used to run in 2010. This version of the Exodia deck focuses on drawing tons of cards, stunning the opponents destroying & negating everything they play until we get the 5 pieces in hand.

Strategy:

The deck must be exactly 40 cards in order not to lower the probability to draw the 5 pieces. The only monsters we play have the ability to retrieve the 5 pieces of Exodia, their effect is triggered in the graveyard so they aren't affected by Skill Drain. We want to buy ourselves some time with cards such as One Day of Peace, Mystic Mine and Torrential Tribute (which triggers our monsters when hits them). Skill Drain should create problems for the opponents that will almost certainly rely on their monsters' effects. For our protection we have Starlight Road and Solemn Judgment, but also Torrential Tribute works well in disrupting the opponents' plans during their turn. Reckless Greed must not be used until you can activate 2 or 3 simultaneously (to skip only 2 draw phases, but drawing 4 or 6 cards) or, alternatively, in desperate situations. Triple Tactics Talent could be sided-out if the opponent doesn't make a big usage of monster effects in our turn.

Possible variations:

Probably more cards to defend from attacks as Quaking Mirror Force could be needed (some testing is required to clarify). In case, could remove 1/2x Triple Tactics Talent and/or 1x Torrential Tribute. A 3rd Triple Tactics Talent could fit well in the deck if needed. The 3x Reckless Greed could be too greedy and may be substituted with 2/3x Dark Bribe in order to have some further protection, especially from cards not triggering Starlight Road. The remaining 1/2x slots could be taken by 1x Obliterate!!! or 1/2x Legacy of Yata-Garasu (or Jar of Greed) or 1x Wall of Revealing Light or 1/2x Messenger of Peace or 1/2x Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring or 1/2x Swords of Revealing Light. Alternatively, instead of using 3x Skill Drain we can afford one more monster, 3x Cyber Valley, and substitute 2x Torrential Tribute with 2x good defending cards as Quaking Mirror Force. One more version could be using cards as There Can Be Only One, Gozen Match and Rivalry of Warlords to block the opponent (maybe substituting Skill Drain and some Torrential Tribute).

Side Deck:

- Messenger of Peace is the most valid spell we kept outside the deck, so it might be added if necessary to defend more - Pot of Avarice / The Transmigration Prophecy is a desperate partial remedy in case the opponent manages to make us discard some pieces - Raigeki, Lightning Storm, Harpie's Feather Duster, Mystical Space Typhoon in case needed depending on the opponent - Floodgate Trap Hole and Quaking Mirror Force in case you want to choose the strategy to flood the opponent field with monsters and stop some combos - Lost Wind and Dark Bribe in case the opponent makes use of specific critical cards to be stopped

Extra Deck:

The only used monster is Stardust Dragon thanks to Starlight Road, but we need it to have 15 cards anyways for the Pot of Prosperity. In case of suggestions and better ideas of monsters that can be actually used in specific situations, please leave a comment and let me know.

A few extra useful cards:

Monsters: - Battle Fader (not awesome since only prevents direct attacks, but still ends the battle phase from the hand) - Swift Scarecrow - Crystal Seer (nice to cycle through the deck fast, but it's a problem with Skill Drain) - Cyber Valley (very strong, but it's a problem with Skill Drain) Spells: - Swords of Revealing Light - Draw of Fate - Terraforming - Field Barrier - Pot of Extravagance - Magical Mallet (one of the best alternatives to Reload, Card Trader, and Card Destruction since you can choose which cards to recycle, but still it's a -1 in hand) Traps: - Legacy of Yata-Garasu - Good Goblin Housekeeping - Jar of Greed - Waboku (good to gain 1 turn, prevents all possible attacks risks) - Dimensional Prison (only stops 1 attack) - Lost Wind - Wall of Revealing Light - Trap Trick - Time Seal Please leave some comments to let me know what you think and take a look at my other decks!

Blue-Eyes is one of the original archetypes of Yu-Gi-Oh! , and is one of the most iconic as well. With the downfall of the dragons, however, most are led to believe that this archetype stands no chance in today's dueling world. WELL NO MORE! This deck can compete with the rest of them, though it doesn't need most of the other support cards - unless you're playing pure. But this deck is combo-based and is keen on Special Summoning as well as searching. You can even play around Nibiru, as you can summon Crystal Wing on the fifth summon (Normal Summon The White Stone of Legend, Special Summon Destrudo, Synchro into Black Rose Moonlight, Use world legacy Guardragon to bring back The White Stone of Legend, then make the Crystal Wing). You can even get spicier with your combos if you get the chance, and even end the game with a classic Neo Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon.

Jet Synchron just got off the list, so I thought I look into Orcust again since they used to play Jet back in the day. And look at that it makes Orcust much more playable. What I want to show you is just the prototype since I don't know the correct ratios yet and I am also considering to go through other engines as well, just as dagda and souls.  The good thing right now is that halq is still legal, so we can use jet as a 1 card halq. But what do we do with halq? It's simple we get bombard and use it and halq to go into gala, then we can shuffle the Jet back and get an Orcust sp/tr. Now if we have an Orcust in hand we can extend further since we have bombard in gy. We also can play brave since we don't need our normal summon anymore, so say goodbye to bricky scrap golem combos.  Btw we can also use Small World, everything we need is a level 3 monster, then we use Terrortop as a bridge and get access to either Jet or Girsu aka the best cards in the deck.  I see alot of potential here and think that Orcust might be a rogue deck if not even a T2 deck. It just needs abit more testing.

deck_excerpt: Abyss actors is the most fun pend deck by a mile, and it is very budget. So you should read this decklist.
deck_description: Abyss Actors are my favorite deck, and they have been getting some good placements recently... well they've been getting any placements, and thats about all I can wish for. The main strategy of abyss actors is going second, as their best cards like comic relief only really work going second.  If you are going second the basic plan is "RISE OF THE ABYSS KING TURBO", the combos you can do are more complicated than this, but its good to keep that idea in mind, because it really is the best card in the deck.  Now, onto the questions you may have: "Why the Mystic Mine in the main, while the going first cards to support it are in the side." There are two reasons, 90% of the time you will be going second the first game, so you don't need your going first cards. The second reason is that it allows you to play around hand traps going second. Say your opponent has a wide board with cards left in the hand. You play mine and it either chews through a spell negate, or it stops them from playing any effects. Then you can do all your combos staying under their cards, and when you are ready to attack, you play RISE OF THE ABYSS KING to destroy your own mine and their monsters. And from that point you'll probably win. If they end their turn on one or two monsters then you can instead side it out for the dark ruler. I would do droplets but those are expensive.  "What do I do going first" Side in everything, summon bagooska, summon sloth, set demise and solemn. Then hope they can't beat that. Else, go to game three.  "Why are you running evil heel, he's not that good and another level 4 would probably be better to help with going into bagooska." True, however Evil Heel is my boyfriend and I love him, so I am going to run him.  "Why the change of heart" It just got unbanned and its a funny going second card, arguably just using comic relief is better, but it will at least chew through a negate, so whatever.  "Why should I play this deck" It's a great deck, and it literally costs like $40ish dollars to build, also the max rarity cards are cheap, so you can look at shiny cardboard for cheap. Also Evil heel is really hot and you should play a deck with him in it. There are literally zero problems with this deck.  "Why not just play metalfoes for a cheap pend deck" It doesn't have evil heel in it.     So as you can see there are exactly zero problems with this deck, so you should totally play it.

deck_description: Sky Striker deck with the add on of a little Toon Engine and DPE.  Toon Engine Explanation: you can use Toon Table of Content to search another Toon Table of content, and continue till you can search for a Toon Cyber Dragon. At that point you can summon it and fusion summon Chimeratech Megafleet Dragon (Toon Cyber Dragon + a monster in the extra field). This way you can remove an opponent's monster without triggering its effect (so its useful against DPE, Herald, Apollousa, etc.) and you will instantly have 3 magic spells in the graveyard.

deck_description: You'll want to get out Rexterm as quickly as you can. Therefore we are running 17 cards that can help us bring him out. Because Ash is a major threat, we opt for Solemn Strike rather than Judgment, as it can ensure the Summon going through, even if halving our LP is generally a good thing. Since we won't do any Special Summoning during our turn, we choose Pot of Duality to aid us in finding something useful off the top, e.g. Strike or Fossil Dig/Misc. You could also use Prosperity, but since I don't want to spend over 300 bucks on a playset, Duality will do just as fine.

deck_excerpt: Best way to play Dark Scorpions (please Konami we want more support)
deck_description:
This deck is a Dark Scorpion deck that is over 300 $ and that can make Apollousa and I:P Masquerena with 2 cards in hand turn 1. Thank you Halqifibrax and Isolde, thank you so much on that. So the 3 card combo for this deck is easy. You need to have any level 4 or lower Dark Scorpion, Fire Flint Lady and "Infernoble Arms - Durendal" in your hand for this combo. Step 1: Normal Summon Dark Scorpion Step 2: Special Summon Fire Flint Lady Step 3: Activate "Infernoble Arms - Durendal" from your hand and automaticaly use it's effect and add Infernoble Knight - Renaud Step 4: Special Summon Infernoble Knight - Renaud so it becomes a tuner Step 5: Use Dark Scorpion and Fire Flint Lady to Link Summon Isolde, Two Tales of Noble Knights and add Infernoble Knight Oliver from your deck to your hand with link monster's effect Step 6: Use other effect of Isolde and send Divine Sword - Phoenix Blade to the graveyard to Special Summon from your deck either Fire Flint Lady or Renaud Step 7: Banish your Dark Scorpion and Fire Flint Lady from your graveyard to add Divine Sword - Phoenix Blade from your grave to your hand Step 8: Discard Phoenix Blade to Special Summon Oliver from your hand Step 9: Use monster you summoned with Isolde's effect and Renaud to Link Summon Halqifibrax and with his effect summon Effect Veiler from either deck or hand Step 10: Link Summon Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess using Halqifibrax and Isolde Step 11: Link Summon I:P Masquerena using Veiler and Oliver Step 12: Banish Oliver and Renaud from grave to add Phoenix Blade to your hand
What did I got from this?

You got Apollousa with 2 negates and I:P Masquerena which, after Apollousa uses it's negates can activate it's effect so you can link summon Knightmare Unicorn and discard Phoenix Blade to shuffle opponent's card into the deck.

This still is a trash deck and it has a lot of problems: 
  • 1 hand trap and you are dead
  • Apollousa is not good in a format with Ogre
  • Forbidden Droplet
  • Kinda bad board for todays meta
  • Dark Scorpions don't do much
  • If goes second can be easily destroyed
  • No good boss monsters for turn 1
Deck still has some pluses, if you get a little bit more lucky hand:
  • Recovery
  • OTK
  • Accesscode turn 2
  • Zeus
  • Traps + Lord of the Heavenly Prison
But yeah I do not think it is good even against Rogue decks, well maybe against Rogues but even there it is kinda bad. It is on you to decide.

The goal of this deck is to flood the field with multiple synchro-based negates. To do this your main goal is to get into Junk Speeder so you can get multiple synchrons on the field so you can go into your bigger monsters such as Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon, Chaos Ruler, Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Abyss (which you go to off of Jet Synchron and Chaos Ruler), and Baronne De Fleur. ALTERNATIVE CHOICES IN THE DECK: Baronne De Fleur can be swapped for F.A. Dawn Dragster If the format requires it, you can switch Stardust Charge Warrior for either Brionic, Dragon Of The Ice Barrier or Infernity Doom Archfiend. This should only be done if the format requires it as the extra draws are very important in the deck. EXPLAINING THE DECK: The Ascator engine is a free Chaos Ruler which helps to make a target for Junk Synchron. Junk Converter is used primarily to get either Junk Synchron or Stardust Synchron. WE DO NOT PLAY TUNING. WE DO NOT NEED IT. Instead, We Use Synchro Overtake. With Synchro Overtake you target the Junk Warrior in your Extra Deck to either add to hand OR SPECIAL SUMMON Junk Synchron. Please note that if you special summon Junk Synchron, it will not get its effect to special a level 2 from grave. The Stardust Synchron engine is a free level 8 and more. It is a pretty self-explanatory engine but has high value. The 3 Emergency Teleportation is huge in this deck. It allows for extended plays and more negates. In this deck, I run Psychic Ace, Psychic Tracker, and Ghost Ogre as targets for Emergency Teleportation. I find that I usually lack non-tuners, but if you feel you need more you can swap the Psychic Tracker for Psychic Wheeleder. Accel Synchron takes a page out of chrystron's book and allows you to synchro summon during your opponent's turn. This is a great way to disrupt them. Because of this immense utility, you should try and keep Accel Synchron and one other level 5 monster on the field so you can synchro summon into Satellite Warrior during your opponent's turn. Satellite Warrior lets you essentially clear your opponent's board, gaining attack for each card it destroys.

deck_excerpt: Demetrius Ishizhu Ishtar Inspired Anime Character Deck ( Duelists Of Proxyene)
deck_description: This is my brand new Ishizhu Ishtar Inspired Anime Character Deck. This mixes her deck with elements of her new support in Duelist Pack : Duelists Of Proxyene. Aromages, or Aroma, archetype is a series of plant monsters that have effects that activate either when you gain LP, if your LP is higher than your opponents, or both. Their archetypal spells are very powerful, and they easily take advantage of Plant support, however they do not have a competent Boss Monster, and essentially have to rely on Ruddy Rose Dragon, which is generic, but meant for plants. While this deck has terrorized low power formats like Duel Links, they fail to actually find success in the TCG or OCG in the modern metagame.  For the decklist, we have an Aroma package of 3x Marjoram, 3x Laurel, 2x Angelica, 3x Gardening, 3x Garden, 2x Blessed Winds, 2x Humid Winds, 2x Sweet Marjoram, and 2x Aromaseraphy Jasmine, my preferred Handtrap lineup of 2x Nibiru, 3x Ash Blossom, 2x Ghost Belle, and 2x Veiler, 1x Carrotweight, 1x Rose Girl, 3x Lonefire Blossom, 1x Spore, 3x Evil Thorn, 1x One for One, 1x Avarice, 1x Terraforming, and 1x Called By, and for the Extra Deck we have 1x Ruddy Rose, 1x Baronne, 1x Borreload Savage, 1x Black Rose, 1x Garden Rose Maiden, 1x Formula Synchron, 1x Underworld Goddess, 1x Accesscode, 1x Knightmare Unicorn, 1x Halqifibrax, 1x Crossrose.

Burning Abyss, or BA for short, is an archetype of Fiend-Type monsters that are very xenophobic, as they destroy themselves if you control a non-BA monster, unless they are negated, such as via Tour Guide, or are protected, such as via Cherubini or Rhino Warrior, and don't have any really good archetypal spells or traps, and have very powerful monster effects. So you know what that means, we're shoving in Sekka's Light, baby!  For the decklist, we have a BA package of 3x Cir, 2x Alich, 1x Farfa, 3x Graff, 3x Scarm, 1x Beatrice, 2x Dante, and 2x Cherubini, my preferred Handtrap lineup of 2x Nibiru, 3x Ash Blossom, 2x Ghost Belle, 3x Maxx C, and 2x Veiler, 2x Fairy Tail - Snow, 3x Rhino Warrior, 3x Tsuchinoko, 3x Tour Guide, 2x Jackalope and 3x Sekka's Light, and for the rest of the Extra Deck, we have 1x Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Abyss, 1x Borreload Savage, 1x Chaos Ruler, 1x Zeus, 1x Downerd, 1x Leviair, 1x Gossip Shadow, 1x Underworld Goddess, 1x Accesscode, and 1x Knightmare Unicorn.

this deck were used from gold V to diamond III, after that i decided to cut the DPE engine since most of the time I drew celestial or dasher, not the fusion destiny  for the decklist i used to diamond I : https://ygoprodeck.com/swordsoul-tenyi-9/  the gameplay:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gev8vUNPB4w  Basic Combo:  1 Card: Swordsoul Emergence search for taia, banish taia, search for swordsoul emergence (if you drew wyrm next turn, you can search mo ye, if you did not search for taia) or swordsoul blackout (for extra disturption).  2 Cards: Swordsoul Mo Ye +1 wyrm bread and butter of swordsoul combo, mo ye would synchro lv 8 chixiao to search for Longyuan and synchro 10 (either baroness or chengying, if you have card effect that banish or destroy your chengying except chixiao such as called by the grave or swordsoul blackout) chengying could be solid option.  2 Tenyi (Ashuna +1 different name Tenyi) Special summon ashuna, link summon monk tenyi, use the second tenyi to SS itself, use ashuna effect to SS the different name from field tenyi (i.e. SS vishuda if you have adhara) synchro to chixiao. Now, you have two route depending on your hand and matchup, against light based opponent, you don't want to banish adhara since you want to use baxia eff to destroy monk of the tenyi and SS adhara. route 1: banish Adhara to add Ashuna from banish, chixiao would search for Mo Ye or Longyuan, Mo Ye will reveal ashuna to synchro lv 8 (baxia or drago berserker of tenyi) or longyuan would discard ashuna to become chengying. route 2: Chixiao search for Taia (no wyrm or swordsoul) or Mo Ye (have another wyrm / swordsoul card), synchro lv 8 baxia then destroy monk of the tenyi to SS adhara from GY, synchro 9 chaofeng lock light  4 card: the combo is pretty similar with 2 card Mo Ye, but you start with Longyuan first to synchro baronne to avoid nibiru, then you will synchro Baronne, then lv 8 chixiao, alternatively you can do this with taia for three hand combo.  Archnemeses Protos: generally not first turn card, except you know you will fight against PK or dark attribute based deck, also a good counter for DPE since it could not be destroyed, would destroy DPE and lock DPE from special summoning. However you either hard draw or have wyrm synchro still on the field to actually search this card with swordsoul emergence. You might tempted to destroy your own chixiao if you know you will fight against light attribute based deck.

a budget live twin deck with staples from recent structure decks + zeus (bc i happened to draw one)

Main strategy: Turbo out Gae Dearg with Remus, Legatus, and Dragon Ravine (easily accessible with cards such as Terraforming and Gold Sarc). Once you have made GD send Zephyros to the GY with his effect. Bounce the Ravine to summon Zephyros and make Romulus, with Romulus search Glow. Glow allows you to get Mystletainn and summon an equipped Dragunity to the field. The monster that you will be equipping with Mystletainn is GD. Since he's not a HOPT you will use him again and summon Baby Roc. Now with Mystletainn and GD XYZ into Atum and summon RedMD from the deck (it's crucial to detach GD from Atum so you can summon him again with newly summoned RedMD). Your field should now contain Atum (preferably in EMZ), RedMD, Baby Roc, and Gae Dearg. If you have a Dragon/Winged Beast in hand, use GD once more to search Stormwinds. Link into Spheres with RedMD and Atum and Synchro into Savage with the leftover monsters. Lastly normal summon Stormwinds. On your opponent's turn if your Stormwinds is outed before the Battle Phase, immediately use Spheres to bounce something and summon Drago from deck to get another floodgate live on the field. Strengths, weaknesses and other comments: The biggest strength of this deck is that it can find pretty much every single card in its deck and the main combo is very consistent so you can often end on Spheres Savage Stormwinds. The biggest weakness is of course Nibiru which is controllable with the Adventure engine. Adventure does so much for the deck, not only does it get you into an Omni-negation but Fateful Adventure lets you discard cards that you want in the GY. Because you run Ravine, Remus, Rite of Aramesir, Gold Sarc, and more, Gamma is often live on your first turn.

deck_excerpt: Pure dinos I used to climb to the highest rank every Master Duel season I participated in/
deck_description: Main Deck: Miscellaneousaurus - Strongest card in this deck. Makes all dinos on the field immune during the Main Phase that you use this (A lot of people don't notice). If the effect from the hand resolves, dinos on field can't get Ash'd, Nibiru'd, or any other typical prevention effect. Normal combo is to send to grave, banish and summon Animadorned Archosaur and combo from there. Souleating Oviraptor - One of the main cards, can make a decent combo alone. Searches any dino from deck. Normal summon then search Miscellaneousaurus and go from there. I also sometimes search Ultimate Conductor Tyranno or a Kaiju if there's a tough to remove monster on the field. Animadorned Archosaur - Usually used on a special summon from Miscellaneousaurus to get Double Evolution Pill and finsh the main combo. You either want to pop a baby dino or Giant Rex.
